			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New Bard- I'm broke!  How can I make money?<a name="55864"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 10 04 9:30 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I found myself in a similar situation not too long ago when returning to EQ (its like an old mistress, still comfortable playing with it after the shine wears off the newer games).
<br />

<br />
Places for a complete newbie to hunt for cash (easy):
<br />

<br />
L1 to L4 North Qeynos Zone - Here you are hunting for Large Rats and the (Black and Red) Snakes.  From the Rats you will loot Eyes, Field Rat Skulls and Plague Rat Tails.  From the snakes you will loot the jawbones and poison sacks (and eggs if you want to sell to players) also one of the skin types sells well to vendors.  Doing just this and selling to the N Qeynos vendors I made 50pp by level 4.
<br />

<br />
L5 to L8 Steamfont - Here you will hunt the Grikbar Kobolds.  There are several camps.  The main one is just off the newbie valley with three groups of tents you can hunt in a circle.  Beware of Bugglegupp when hunting the tents along the zone wall.  The Kobolds are not social at all, you can attack one and the others will not add.  Pull them away from the camp a little so you can twist in your CoD and kill them faster.  You will loot the Grikbar Kobold Furs, Kobold Teeth and the Steamfont Water from these (you can loot the armor pieces if you wish, if you have space).  Do not sell here, these items stack, get back to your home zone where you have better faction to make the most profit.  The furs sell for almost a plat and the teeth for about 5 gold.  Both are stackable.  From 5 to 8 you should get about 2 stacks each of Furrs and Teeth.  Around another 60pp or so.
<br />

<br />
8-12 Use this time to work on your newbie armor quests.  Go shopping in the bazaar and look for good value items on weapons (1HB, 1HS and Piercing).  Items I found for under 50pp were Velium Short Blade (1HS 10/24 50pp) Crystalline Spider Fang (Piercing 10/22 20pp) and a Guardian Mace (1HB 14/24 40pp).  Do not waste money on armor at this point.  Your newbie armor will be more than sufficient.
<br />

<br />
12-15 East or West Commonlands, Qeynos Hills, Eruds Crossing.  Your target here are Willowwisps.  If going to Eruds Crossing (recommended) look out for the Mad Island Hermit.  He is highly aggressive and will kill you if you are not 100% going into the fight with him.  Your loot is the lightstones and greater lightstones.  Sell the lightstones to the vendor, take the Greater Lightstones to the Gypsy Camp in NK (when level 16) The Concordance of Research you receive in return will sell for 9pp.  You should be able to gather 20 to 25 Greater Lightstones by L16.  Another 200pp or so in the bank.
<br />

<br />
16-20 Warrens.  Probably the most underutilized zone in the game.  You will head to the Prince Room here.  Until you get there, none of the Kobolds will agro on you, outside the prince room you will encounter 3 kobolds on duty at the arches, these you will lull and single pull to the corner.  Lull and single pull the guards around the prince room too.  Do not pull the prince until about L18, he has a HT that is relatively nasty up to that point.  When pulling him make sure you are 100%.  Your loot here, all bronze weapons (you can disregard the Wakisashi and the small dagger here as they only sell for small amounts) most sell for 2pp to 4pp, some as high as 6pp.  You can easily make another 200-400pp in your time in the Warrens.
<br />

<br />
There you go, all solo and for the most part no competition in these spots.  All appropriate experience for your level.
<br />

<br />
At L20 you can go to the bazaar and shop for bargains in Armor to upgrade your Newbie stuff.  You should be looking for cheap Lambent or Cheap Ry`Gorr armor.  As an alternate breastplate Netherbian Chitin is always cheap.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
